# Locked Prose

## Opening

Every note begins with exactly two sentences:

`The RBT met with [CLIENT_REFERRAL] and [CaregiverList] to implement program targets.`

Then exactly one environmental sentence:

- No changes: `There have been no environmental changes recently.`
- Changes: `There have been environmental changes recently.`

`CLIENT_REFERRAL` is the profile first name when present, otherwise `the client`. The opening does
not name the meeting place.

## Clinical body

The body contains exactly one model-written ABC paragraph per billable session hour. Each paragraph
must include the exact replacement program assigned in the app for that hour and the exact percentage
selected in the app. No other clinical-body prose or pairing rule is locked.

## Closing paragraph

The server builds the closing with `buildLockedClosingParagraph`. Its fixed tail is:

`There were no health or safety concerns during the visit. The RBT will continue working with the client as outlined in the Behavior Plan. All data on maladaptive behaviors and progress in program implementation was collected during the session in accordance with the BIP. The session was completed as planned.`

The first closing sentence always uses plain:

`praise (e.g., "Good job," "Wow," and "Good attention to detail")`

and the server-approved preferred-items clause.

## End sequence

After the closing paragraph:

1. Server-built performance sentence.
2. `The next session is tentatively scheduled for [MM/DD/YYYY].`, or
   `The next session is tentatively scheduled; the date is to be determined.`

Nothing is appended after the next-session sentence.
